The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | India to be based in Karachi
                                                                                                                                                                                           India to be based in Karachi
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      
	Bangalore: Team India will be based in Karachi during the forthcoming Asia Cup and, as the final too is in that port city, the Mahendra Singh Dhonis wont have to travel anywhere else in Pakistan.         
	India, Pakistan and Hong Kong will be in Karachi, while Sri Lanka, Bangladesh and the UAE will be in Lahore, the Asian Cricket Councils long-serving chief executive, Syed Ashraful Huq, told The Telegraph.         
	The tournament, last hosted by Sri Lanka almost four years ago, will be held from June 24 to July 6.                                                                                                                          
